.TH "cs4270_hw_params" 9 "cs4270_hw_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cs4270_hw_params \- program the CS4270 with the given hardware parameters.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cs4270_hw_params
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
the audio stream
.IP "params" 12
the hardware parameters to set
.IP "dai" 12
the SOC DAI (ignored)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function programs the hardware with the values provided.
Specifically, the sample rate and the data format.

The .ops functions are used to provide board-specific data, like input
frequencies, to this driver.  This function takes that information,
combines it with the hardware parameters provided, and programs the
hardware accordingly.
